# Natural Conversation Flow Patterns

## Overview

This rule documents patterns for creating natural, context-aware conversations that avoid robotic responses and repetitive information requests. Based on real-world improvements to deposit intent handling.

## Core Principles

### 1. Context Awareness Over Repetition
**Never ask for information already provided in the conversation.**

```typescript
// ❌ Bad: Ignoring context
User: "I want to use the ultra-safe strategy"
Agent: "Please specify which strategy you'd like to use."

// ✅ Good: Building on context
User: "I want to use the ultra-safe strategy" 
Agent: "Great choice on the ultra-safe strategy! Which token would you like to deposit?"
```

### 2. User Voice in Suggestions
**Write suggestions as the user would speak, not as the agent.**

```typescript
// ❌ Bad: Agent voice
suggestions = [
  { label: "Specify amount", text: "Please specify the amount to deposit" }
];

// ✅ Good: User voice  
suggestions = [
  { label: "Deposit 100 USDC", text: "I want to deposit 100 USDC into the Ultra-Safe strategy" }
];
```

### 3. Real Values Over Placeholders
**Use realistic amounts and tokens users would actually type.**

```typescript
// ❌ Bad: Placeholder text
"I want to deposit [amount] USDC into the [strategy]"

// ✅ Good: Real values
"I want to deposit 100 USDC into the Ultra-Safe strategy"
```

## Implementation Patterns

### Context-Aware Parameter Handling

#### Missing Parameter Handler Pattern
```typescript
async function handleMissingParameters(intentContext, missingParam) {
  const { returnData } = intentContext;
  const { strategyName, tokenSymbol, amount } = returnData || {};
  
  // Build response using known context
  if (missingParam === "token" && strategyName) {
    return `Great choice on the ${strategyName}! Which token would you like to deposit? You can use USDC, ETH, or other tokens from your portfolio.`;
  }
  
  if (missingParam === "amount" && strategyName && tokenSymbol) {
    return `Perfect! How much ${tokenSymbol} would you like to deposit into the ${strategyName}? You can specify an amount like "100 USDC" or "0.1 ETH".`;
  }
  
  // Fallback for no context
  return `I'd be happy to help you with your deposit. Could you tell me which strategy and token you'd like to use?`;
}
```

#### Context Extraction Pattern
```typescript
// Extract conversation context for smart responses
const conversationContext = {
  extractFromHistory: (messages) => ({
    mentionedStrategy: extractStrategyMentions(messages),
    mentionedTokens: extractTokenMentions(messages), 
    mentionedAmounts: extractAmountMentions(messages),
    userPreferences: inferPreferences(messages)
  }),
  
  buildContextualResponse: (context, missingParam) => {
    // Use extracted context to avoid repetitive questions
    if (context.mentionedStrategy && missingParam === "token") {
      return `I see you're interested in ${context.mentionedStrategy}. Which token would you like to use?`;
    }
  }
};
```

### Natural Suggestion Generation

#### Realistic Amount Patterns
```typescript
const REALISTIC_AMOUNTS = {
  USDC: ["10", "50", "100", "200", "500", "1000"],
  ETH: ["0.01", "0.05", "0.1", "0.25", "0.5", "1.0"],
  WETH: ["0.1", "0.25", "0.5", "1.0", "2.0"],
};

const generateNaturalSuggestions = (availableTokens, strategies) => {
  return strategies.map(strategy => {
    const token = selectAppropriateToken(availableTokens, strategy);
    const amount = selectRealisticAmount(token);
    
    return {
      label: `Deposit ${amount} ${token}`,
      text: `I want to deposit ${amount} ${token} into the ${strategy.name}`
    };
  });
};
```

